    <node id="entity:a485dd67852d2a5d276b">
      <data key="d0">entity:a485dd67852d2a5d276b</data>
      <data key="d1">PERSON</data>
      <data key="d6">Alan Turing</data>
      <data key="d7">Alan Turing was a pioneering British mathematician, logician, and computer scientist, born in London in 1912. He is considered the father of theoretical computer science and artificial intelligence, having made foundational contributions to both fields as well as to mathematical biology. During World War II, he worked at Bletchley Park, where he developed the Bombe and played a crucial role in breaking the Enigma code. After the war, he continued his influential work at the National Physical Laboratory and the University of Manchester.</data>
      <data key="d9">0.008066</data>
      <data key="d10">1.0</data>
      <data key="d11" />
    </node>
